{
  "texts": [
    "ML consists of unsupervised learning, supervised learning, and reinforcement learning.",
    "Through traditional unsupervised learning, we can investigate the intrinsic structure of the unlabeled dataset (X), mine the correlations between variables, then conclude the underlying rules of the data, and draw insightful conclusions 10, for example principal component analysis, hierarchical clustering and generative models.",
    "In terms of generative unsupervised learning, the Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN) 11, Variational Autoencoder (VAE) 12 and Denoising Diffusion Probabilistic Models (DDPM) 13 are developed to learn from the unlabeled dataset and extract the hidden features.",
    "Recent literature reports the success of embedding the object-aware SE(3) diffusion model to generate the accurate transition state of catalysts in reactions 14.",
    "The widely discussed large language model (LLM), ChatGPT is also based on a large generative pre-trained transformer and diffusion models."
  ]
}